notes:
Hello Singari, Jesus Sr. and Jesus Jr. stopped by this afternoon to investigate the latest irrigation situation. They did see that the water was running and found where the issue is so the good news is that they can easily fix it! What they found is that you have 6 valves in your valve box; 4 of them are new, but 2 of them are old. It is one of the two old ones that is causing the issue. These valves do wear out over time and they are cheaper to replace entirely than take them apart to investigate what went wrong. As long as they would replace one of them, they are recommending to go ahead and replace both to prevent this issue from happening again in the near future. As far as they can tell, this is not anything directly related to the previous irrigation work.

Your irrigation system is set to run Tuesday early morning and Friday early morning, which is why you noticed the excess water today. The system probably turned on early this morning and the one valve that waters the window box and planters never shut off. To stop the water, Jesus turned the system off this afternoon when he stopped by. The rest of your irrigation system will not be impacted as long as they come back to turn it back on in the next two days, which they are available to do. Please let us know if you would like to proceed with the repairs. The cost for each new valve, installed is $75, or both valves for $150.
Please make a note of which areas are not covered by irrigation and quote to convert to drip - I will send the blueprint.

Hi Janine,

No problem, we will have him come out tomorrow to check on that head.

When I consulted with Jesus regarding the current leak, he explained that he installed 1804 rain bird Sam prs sprinklers heads, which have check valves built in. By installing this head, the leaking should have stopped. The valve might have a small leak and water is passing through causing the sprinklers to leak but the head should not be allowing the water to flow through the sprinkler when the system is off.

If it's determined tomorrow that the head itself is faulty, incorrectly installed, etc., we will absolutely complete the visit complimentary. If it's determined that it's actually a related valve or something that is not related to the actual head itself, we will have to charge for the visit.
